						               													<description>PocketStalingrad is a print-and-play game for two players (see the files section below). By David Laufle The game is free, and might even fit in your pocket. &amp;#10;It's 1942 in war torn Russia, head into the besieged city of Stalingrad and fight your way to victory in 30-45 minutes. The game uses several dice. Roll the dice and set aside unit deployment, tactics, events or command points, using at least one die per roll. Add units to the 5 major city locations or to Gumrak Airfield or the Volga Crossing, add in Fortifications, Pioneers, snipers, infiltration, Luftwaffe attacks, night, Guards and more; and you have yourself a battle.&amp;#10;Control of 3 of the 5 major locations by turn 5 is a winner, otherwise the most City Areas wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
